    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/comment_edittext6"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:hint="Tuberculosis \n \n
Tuberculosis is a potentially serious infectious disease caused by the bacterium Mycobacterium tuberculosis. It primarily affects the lungs but can also affect other parts of the body. \n \n

Symptoms \n \n
•Cought lasting more that three weeks \n
•Chest pain \n
•Coughing up blood or sputum \n
•Night sweats \n
•Weight loss \n \n

Treatment \n \n
•Antibiotic treatment for several months \n
•Combination of different Antibiotics \n
•Treatment must be completed to prevent drug resistance \n \n"
        android:gravity="start"
        android:inputType="none"
        android:lines="5"
        android:minLines="3"
        android:maxLines="10"
        android:textStyle="bold"
        android:scrollbars="vertical"/>

    <Button
